00:00:01:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:01:040000.Dialogue: You know, I've been thinking about timetravel again.

00:00:03:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:03:230000.Dialogue: Why? Did you hit a roadblock with invisibility?

00:00:10:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:10:090000.Dialogue: Anyway. It occurs to me, If I have ever did perfect time machine, I'd just go into the past and give it to myself. That's eliminating the need for me to invent it in the first place.

00:00:21:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:21:100000.Dialogue: Yeah, it really kicks the pressure off.

00:00:24:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:24:140000.Dialogue: Sounds like a breakthrough. Should I call Science Magazine and tell them to hold the cover?

00:00:28:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:28:210000.Dialogue: It's time travel, I will have already done that.

00:00:32:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:32:230000.Dialogue: Then I guess congratulations are in order.

00:00:35:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:35:070000.Dialogue: No, congratulations will have been in order.

00:00:39:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:39:050000.Dialogue: You know, I am not going to enjoy this party.

00:00:41:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:41:090000.Dialogue: I know, I'm familiar with you.

00:00:43:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:43:170000.Dialogue: The last department party, Professor Finkleday cornered me and talked about spelunking for 45 minutes.

00:00:50:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:50:070000.Dialogue: You know what's interesting about caves?

00:00:55:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:55:190000.Dialogue: Then we'll avoid him, we'll meet the new department head, congratulate him, shake his hand and go.

00:01:00:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:00:030000.Dialogue: How's this? Pleased to meet you, Dr. Gablehauser. How fortunate for you that the university's chosen to hire you, despite the fact that you've done no original research in 25 years, and instead have written a series of popular books that reduce the great concepts of science to a series of anecdotes, each one dumbed down to accommodate the duration of an average bowel movement.

00:01:28:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:28:050000.Dialogue: You know there only eight consonants in Hawaiian language?

00:01:30:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:30:160000.Dialogue: Interesting. You should lead with that.

00:01:35:080000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:01:35:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:35:080000.Dialogue: Oh, God, look at this buffet.

00:01:38:020000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:01:38:020000.Speaker: Raj

00:01:39:190000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:01:39:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:39:190000.Dialogue: You don't have buffets in India?

00:01:41:110000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:01:41:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:41:110000.Dialogue: Of course, but it's all Indian food.

00:01:44:150000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:01:44:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:44:150000.Dialogue: You can't find a bagel in Mumbai to save your life. Shmear me.

00:01:50:210000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:01:50:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:50:210000.Dialogue: - Here's an interesting turn of events.

00:01:56:030000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:01:56:030000.Speaker: Leonard

00:01:57:110000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:01:57:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:57:110000.Dialogue: A more plausible explanation is that his work in robotics has made an amazing leap forward.

00:02:03:030000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:03:030000.Speaker: Howard

00:02:07:110000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:07:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:07:110000.Dialogue: May I introduce my special lady friend Summer?

00:02:10:140000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:10:140000.Speaker: Summer

00:02:14:230000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:14:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:14:230000.Dialogue: Here comes our new boss. Be polite.

00:02:17:190000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:17:190000.Speaker: Gablehouser

00:02:20:090000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:20:090000.Speaker: Howard

00:02:22:070000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:22:070000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:02:22:070000.Dialogue: Nice to meet you. And you are?

00:02:24:200000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:24:200000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:02:30:100000.Scene: The department party. Sheldon, Raj and Leonard are at the buffet table.
00:02:30:100000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:02:33:080000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building. Sheldon is carrying a box of his things.
00:02:33:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:33:080000.Dialogue: I can't believe he fired me.

00:02:36:040000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building. Sheldon is carrying a box of his things.
00:02:36:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:36:040000.Dialogue: Well, you did call him a glorified high school science teacher whose last successful experiment was lighting his own farts.

00:02:43:150000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building. Sheldon is carrying a box of his things.
00:02:43:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:43:150000.Dialogue: In my defense, I prefaced that by saying, With all due respect.

00:03:13:220000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:13:220000.Speaker: Leonard

00:03:15:060000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:15:060000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:03:16:200000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:16:200000.Speaker: Leonard

00:03:18:210000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:18:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:18:210000.Dialogue: This isn't breakfast, it's an experiment.

00:03:23:120000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:23:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:23:120000.Dialogue: 'Cause it looks a lot like breakfast.

00:03:25:200000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:25:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:25:200000.Dialogue: I finally have time to test my hypothesis about the separation of the water molecules from the egg proteins and its impact vis-a-vis taste.

00:03:34:170000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:34:170000.Speaker: Leonard

00:03:37:000000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:37:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:37:000000.Dialogue: I look forward to your work with bacon.

00:03:39:060000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:39:060000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:03:42:030000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:42:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:42:030000.Dialogue: You know, I'm sure if you just apologize to Gablehauser, he would give you your job back.

00:03:46:110000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:46:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:46:110000.Dialogue: I don't want my job back. I've spent the past three and a half years staring at grease boards full of equations. Before that, I spent four years working on my thesis. Before that, I was in college, and before that, I was in the fifth grade.

00:03:59:170000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:03:59:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:59:170000.Dialogue: This is my first day off in decades and I'm going to savor it.

00:04:05:170000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:04:05:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:05:170000.Dialogue: I'll let you get back to fixing your eggs.

00:04:07:230000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:04:07:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:07:230000.Dialogue: Not just fixing my eggs, I'm fixing everyone's eggs.

00:04:11:100000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:04:11:100000.Speaker: Leonard

00:04:25:000000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.

00:04:44:130000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:04:44:130000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:04:50:230000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:04:50:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:50:230000.Dialogue: I'm running out to the market. You need anything?

00:04:54:040000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:04:54:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:54:040000.Dialogue: This would be one of those circumstances that people unfamiliar with the law of large numbers would call a coincidence.

00:05:00:020000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:05:00:020000.Speaker: Penny

00:05:03:090000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:05:03:090000.Speaker: Penny

00:05:09:220000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:05:09:220000.Speaker: Penny

00:05:11:060000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon is in the kitchen cooking, Leonard enters.
00:05:11:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:11:060000.Dialogue: Never mind. You won't get it right. I'd better come with you.

00:05:22:000000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:22:000000.Dialogue: How come you didn't go into work today?

00:05:24:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:24:070000.Dialogue: I'm taking a sabbatical because I won't kowtow to mediocre minds.

00:05:31:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:31:030000.Dialogue: Theoretical physicists do not get canned... but yeah.

00:05:37:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:37:040000.Dialogue: Maybe it's all for the best. I always say when one door closes, another one opens.

00:05:44:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:44:040000.Dialogue: Not unless the two doors are connected by relays - or there are motion sensors involved.

00:05:49:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:49:050000.Dialogue: Or if the first door closing creates a change of air pressure that acts upon the second door.

00:06:01:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:01:050000.Dialogue: You're not leaving yourself enough space between cars.

00:06:12:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:12:230000.Dialogue: I'm sorry. Did I insult you? Is your body mass somehow tied into your self-worth?

00:06:19:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:19:200000.Dialogue: Interesting. Anyway, that gives us a total weight of, let's say 4,400 pounds.

00:06:26:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:26:220000.Dialogue: Fine. We're traveling forward at-- good Lord-- 51 miles an hour.

00:06:32:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:32:070000.Dialogue: Let's assume that your brakes are new and the calipers are aligned. Still, by the time we come to a stop, we'll be occupying the same space as that Buick in front of us, an impossibility that nature will quickly resolve into death, mutilation... Oh, look, they built a new putt-putt course.

00:06:50:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:50:040000.Dialogue: This is great. Look at me. I'm in the real world of ordinary people just living their ordinary, colorless workaday lives.

00:07:06:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:06:210000.Dialogue: You want to hear an interesting thing about tomatoes?

00:07:09:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:09:070000.Dialogue: No, not really. Listen, didn't you say you need some eggs?

00:07:13:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:13:170000.Dialogue: Yes, but anyone who knows anything about the dynamics of bacterial growth knows to pick up their refrigerated food on the way out of the supermarket.

00:07:20:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:20:190000.Dialogue: Okay, then maybe you should start heading on out then.

00:07:24:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:24:090000.Dialogue: No, this is fun. Oh, the thing about tomatoes-- and I think you'll really enjoy this-- is they're shelved with the vegetables, but they're technically a fruit.

00:07:34:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:34:140000.Dialogue: No, I mean what you find enjoyable.

00:07:46:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:46:060000.Dialogue: Well, there's some value to taking a multivitamin, but the human body can only absorb so much. What you're buying here are the ingredients for very expensive urine.

00:07:56:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:56:210000.Dialogue: Well, maybe that's what I was going for.

00:08:08:130000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:08:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:08:130000.Dialogue: That was fun. Maybe tomorrow we can go to one of those big warehouse stores.

00:08:12:190000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:12:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:12:190000.Dialogue: Oh, I don't know. It's going to take me a while to recover from all the fun I had today.

00:08:18:200000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:18:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:18:200000.Dialogue: Are you sure? There are a lot of advantages to buying in bulk. For example, I noticed that you purchase your tampons one-month supply at a time.

00:08:28:230000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:28:230000.Speaker: Penny

00:08:30:130000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:30:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:30:130000.Dialogue: Think about it. It's a product that doesn't spoil and you're going to be needing them for at least the next 30 years.

00:08:36:170000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:36:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:36:170000.Dialogue: You want me to buy 30 years worth of tampons?

00:08:40:030000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:40:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:40:030000.Dialogue: Well, 30, 35. When did your mother go into menopause?

00:08:44:170000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:44:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:44:170000.Dialogue: I'm not talking about this with you.

00:08:47:200000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:08:47:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:47:200000.Dialogue: This is a natural human process, and we're talking about statistically significant savings. Now, if you assume 15 tampons per cycle and a 28-day cycle... Are you fairly regular?

00:09:02:140000.Scene: On the stairwell of the apartment building.
00:09:02:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:02:140000.Dialogue: Okay, no warehouse store, but we're still on for putt-putt golf, right?

00:09:12:070000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:12:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:12:070000.Dialogue: Hey, I just ran into Penny. She seemed upset about something.

00:09:15:090000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:15:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:15:090000.Dialogue: I think it's her time of the month.

00:09:19:200000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:19:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:19:200000.Dialogue: I marked the calendar for future reference.

00:09:25:160000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:25:160000.Speaker: Leonard

00:09:28:040000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:28:040000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:09:31:010000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:31:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:31:010000.Dialogue: What happened to your scrambled egg research?

00:09:33:020000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:33:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:33:020000.Dialogue: Oh, that was a dead end. Scrambled eggs are as good as they're ever going to be.

00:09:37:230000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:37:230000.Speaker: Leonard

00:09:41:190000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:41:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:41:190000.Dialogue: I read an article about Japanese scientists who inserted DNA from luminous jellyfish into other animals, and I thought, Hey, fish nightlights.

00:09:53:110000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:53:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:53:110000.Dialogue: Fish nightlights? It's a billion-dollar idea.

00:09:59:060000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:09:59:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:59:060000.Dialogue: Mum's the word. Are you sure you don't want to just apologize to Gablehauser and get your job back?

00:10:07:030000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:10:07:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:07:030000.Dialogue: No, I have too much to do.

00:10:09:230000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:10:09:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:09:230000.Dialogue: Like luminous fish. I'm sorry. I didn't...

00:10:15:120000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:10:15:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:15:120000.Dialogue: That's just the beginning. I also have an idea for a bulk mail-order feminine hygiene company.

00:10:21:080000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:10:21:080000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:10:26:170000.Scene: The apartment, Sheldon has several bowls containing goldfish.
00:10:26:170000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:10:32:150000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:10:32:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:32:150000.Dialogue: Thanks for coming on such short notice.

00:10:34:160000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:10:34:160000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:10:34:160000.Dialogue: - You did the right thing calling.

00:10:47:140000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:10:47:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:47:140000.Dialogue: This is a particularly disturbing one.

00:10:53:010000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:10:53:010000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:10:55:050000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:10:55:050000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper

00:11:07:110000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:07:110000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:11:07:110000.Dialogue: Oh, you got yourself a loom? How nice!

00:11:11:080000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:11:080000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:11:12:120000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:12:120000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:11:12:120000.Dialogue: Honey, why'd you get a loom?

00:11:15:170000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:15:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:15:170000.Dialogue: I was working with luminous fish, and I thought... loom.

00:11:24:130000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:24:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:24:130000.Dialogue: Mom, what are you doing here?

00:11:26:200000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:26:200000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper

00:11:28:140000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:28:140000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:11:30:150000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:30:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:30:150000.Dialogue: Because one of the great minds of the 21st century is raising glow-in-the-dark fish and weaving serapes.

00:11:37:080000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:37:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:37:080000.Dialogue: This is not a serape, this is a poncho. A serape is open at the sides; a poncho is closed.

00:11:42:020000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:42:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:42:020000.Dialogue: This is a poncho. And neither is a reason to call someone'smother.

00:11:47:170000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:47:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:47:170000.Dialogue: Really? When was the last time you left the house?

00:11:50:210000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:50:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:50:210000.Dialogue: I went to the market with Penny.

00:11:52:120000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:52:120000.Speaker: Leonard

00:11:54:090000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:11:54:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:54:090000.Dialogue: Well, then buckle up. In the next four to eight days she's going to get very crabby.

00:12:01:080000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:12:01:080000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:12:01:080000.Dialogue: Sweetheart, your little friend is concerned about you.

00:12:04:080000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:12:04:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:04:080000.Dialogue: Yes, well, I'm not a child-- I'm a grown man, capable of living my life as I see fit. And I certainly don't need someone telling on me to my mother!

00:12:13:080000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:12:13:080000.Speaker: Leonard]

00:12:14:200000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:12:14:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:14:200000.Dialogue: To my room. And no one's allowed in!

00:12:19:170000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:12:19:170000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:12:19:170000.Dialogue: He gets his temper from his daddy. He's got my eyes.

00:12:23:190000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:12:23:190000.Speaker: Leonard

00:12:25:050000.Scene: The stairwell of the apartment building.
00:12:25:050000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:12:25:050000.Dialogue: All that science stuff, that comes from Jesus.

00:12:31:190000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:12:31:190000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:12:35:110000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:12:35:110000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:12:35:110000.Dialogue: Don't trouble yourself. He's stubborn. He may stay in there till the Rapture.

00:12:41:090000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:12:41:090000.Speaker: Penny

00:12:43:170000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:12:43:170000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:12:43:170000.Dialogue: I tell you, I love the boy to death, but he has been difficult since he fell out of me at the K-Mart.

00:12:51:110000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:12:51:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:51:110000.Dialogue: Excuse me for being so bold, but I now see where Sheldon gets his smoldering good looks.

00:12:58:100000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:12:58:100000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:12:58:100000.Dialogue: Honey, that ain't gonna work, but you keep tryin'.

00:13:02:060000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:13:02:060000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:13:02:060000.Dialogue: I made chicken. I hope that isn't one of the animals that you people think is magic.

00:13:14:060000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:13:14:060000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:13:14:060000.Dialogue: You know, we have an Indian gentleman at our church, a Dr. Patel-- It's a beautiful story. The Lord spoke to him and moved him to give us all 20% off on Lasik-- You know, those that needed it.

00:13:26:140000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:13:26:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:26:140000.Dialogue: That is a lovely story. Are we gonna do anything about Sheldon?

00:13:30:080000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:13:30:080000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:13:30:080000.Dialogue: Oh, we will. You have to take your time with Sheldon. His father, God rest his soul, used to always say to me, Mary, you have to take your time with Sheldon.

00:13:39:150000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:13:39:150000.Speaker: Leonard

00:13:46:130000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:13:46:130000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:13:46:130000.Dialogue: So, everybody grab a plate and a pretty place mat that Shelly wove.

00:13:52:030000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:13:52:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:52:030000.Dialogue: Has Shelly ever freaked out like this before?

00:13:54:090000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:13:54:090000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:13:54:090000.Dialogue: Oh, all the time. I remember one summer when he was 13, he built a small nuclear reactor in the shed and told everybody he was gonna provide free electricity for the whole town. Well, the only problem was, he had no what you call fissionable materials.

00:14:10:060000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:10:060000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:14:10:060000.Dialogue: Anyway, when he went on the Internets to get some, a man from the government came by and sat him down real gentle, and told him it's against the law to have yellow-cake uranium in a shed.

00:14:22:200000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:22:200000.Speaker: Penny

00:14:29:110000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:29:110000.Speaker: Leonard

00:14:30:170000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:30:170000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:14:30:170000.Dialogue: That's what he called it. Didn't even slow down the neighbor kids.

00:14:35:110000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:35:110000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:14:35:110000.Dialogue: It pissed our dog off to no end.

00:14:39:170000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:39:170000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:14:39:170000.Dialogue: You know, you two make a cute couple.

00:14:43:150000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:43:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:43:150000.Dialogue: No. We're not... we're not-not a couple. We're singles. Two singles. Like those... individuly wrapped slices of cheese that...

00:14:52:170000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:52:170000.Speaker: Leonard

00:14:55:110000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:55:110000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:14:55:110000.Dialogue: - Did I pluck a nerve there?

00:14:58:010000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:14:58:010000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:14:58:010000.Dialogue: All right, everybody, it's time to eat. Oh, Lord, we thank You for this meal and all of Your bounty.

00:15:06:150000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:15:06:150000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:15:06:150000.Dialogue: And we pray that You help Sheldon get back on his rocker. Now, after a moment of silent meditation, I'm gonna end with In Jesus' name, but you two don't feel any obligation to join in.

00:15:19:160000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:15:19:160000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:15:19:160000.Dialogue: Unless, of course, the Holy Spirit moves you.

00:15:32:000000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:15:32:000000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:32:000000.Dialogue: Oh, my God, this is the best cobbler I've ever had.

00:15:34:190000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:15:34:190000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:15:34:190000.Dialogue: It was always Sheldon's favorite. You know what the secret ingredient is?

00:15:38:230000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:15:38:230000.Speaker: Penny

00:15:45:180000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:15:45:180000.Speaker: Howard

00:15:47:120000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:15:47:120000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper

00:15:51:000000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:15:51:000000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:15:51:000000.Dialogue: He's like a baby deer. You got to let him come to you.

00:16:02:020000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:16:02:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:02:020000.Dialogue: This is ridiculous. Damn it, Sheldon, snap out of it! You're a physicist-- You belong at the university doing research, not hiding in your room!

00:16:17:040000.Scene: Everyone but Sheldon is in the kitchen of the apartment.
00:16:17:040000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper

00:16:25:030000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:25:030000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper

00:16:28:120000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:28:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:16:29:210000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:29:210000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:16:29:210000.Dialogue: Well, that looks awful fancy. What is that?

00:16:33:230000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:33:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:33:230000.Dialogue: It's my idea of what DNA would look like in a silicon-based life-form.

00:16:39:150000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:39:150000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:16:39:150000.Dialogue: But intelligently designed by a creator, right?

00:16:45:200000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:45:200000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:16:47:130000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:47:130000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:16:47:130000.Dialogue: You know how your daddy used to say that you can only fish for so long before you got to throw a stick of dynamite in the water?

00:16:55:200000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:55:200000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper

00:16:59:110000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:16:59:110000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper

00:17:00:160000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:17:00:160000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:06:120000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:17:06:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:13:200000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:17:13:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:13:200000.Dialogue: I'm not going to apologize-- I didn't say anything that wasn't true.

00:17:16:170000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:17:16:170000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:17:16:170000.Dialogue: Now, you listen here. I have been telling you since you were four years old, it's okay to be smarter than everybody, but you can't go around pointing it out.

00:17:24:230000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:17:24:230000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:29:050000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:17:29:050000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:17:29:050000.Dialogue: Remember all the ass-kickings you got from the neighbor kids?

00:17:34:210000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:17:34:210000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:17:34:210000.Dialogue: Now, let's get crackin'. Shower, shirt, shoes, and let's shove off.

00:17:42:060000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. He is building a model of some kind of double helix. There is a knock on the door.
00:17:42:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:42:060000.Dialogue: There wouldn't have been any ass-kickings if that stupid death ray had worked.

00:17:55:160000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:17:55:160000.Dialogue: Leonard, the Lord never gives us more than we can handle. Thankfully, He blessed me with two other children who are dumb as soup.

00:18:08:130000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:18:08:130000.Dialogue: Excuse me, Dr. Gablehauser, are you busy?

00:18:21:090000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:18:21:090000.Dialogue: Let's go, baby. We're losing daylight.

00:18:28:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:28:030000.Dialogue: As you know, several weeks ago in our first encounter, we may have gotten off on the wrong foot when I called you an idiot.

00:18:37:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:37:090000.Dialogue: And I just wanted to say that I was wrong... to point it out.

00:18:44:220000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:18:44:220000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, we haven't been introduced.

00:18:50:120000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:18:50:120000.Dialogue: Now, that's impossible! You must have had him when you were a teenager.

00:18:53:220000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:18:53:220000.Dialogue: Oh, aren't you sweet. His father's dead.

00:19:25:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:25:130000.Dialogue: It involves a part of the human experience that has always eluded me.

00:19:36:000000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Mrs Cooper is tucking him in.
00:19:36:000000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
00:19:36:000000.Dialogue: I'm very proud of you honey. You showed a lot of courage today.

00:19:40:100000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Mrs Cooper is tucking him in.
00:19:40:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:40:100000.Dialogue: Thanks, Mom. Is Dr. Gablehauser going to be my new daddy?

00:19:54:030000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Mrs Cooper is tucking him in.
00:19:54:030000.Speaker: Mrs Cooper
